WEBVTT

00:01.040 --> 00:02.644
I need to go away for a while.

00:02.800 --> 00:04.290
(VOICE BREAKING)
You mean, like a yoga retreat?

00:04.360 --> 00:07.728
How do you feel about tracking
global profit flows in Switzerland?

00:07.960 --> 00:10.725
You weren't the only scientist
I bought, were you?

00:11.360 --> 00:12.361
COADY: Susan.

00:12.720 --> 00:15.690
He's losing his grip.
He's going to destroy everything.

00:16.800 --> 00:19.280
KIRA: <i>Mum, [have a new codename
for the island.</i>

00:19.560 --> 00:20.561
Wonderland.

00:20.760 --> 00:22.842
And if I have to, I'll hustle Rachel.

00:22.920 --> 00:23.921
(DOOR OPENING)

00:24.360 --> 00:25.361
Virginia.

00:25.440 --> 00:27.966
She was trying to kill you.

00:28.160 --> 00:29.400
<i>CHARLOTTE". I don't think they're coming.</i>

00:33.440 --> 00:35.522
There will come a day when you need us.

00:35.640 --> 00:36.641
RACHEL: Come.

00:36.720 --> 00:37.721
Good girl.

00:39.960 --> 00:41.007
It isn't a glitch.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.207
<i>Someone's trying to show me something.</i>

00:50.720 --> 00:53.291
Understanding the human genome

00:53.360 --> 00:55.886
and the environmental impact on genes

00:55.960 --> 00:59.169
is the holy grail of life extension.

00:59.520 --> 01:02.126
While I still can't tell you
the exact number

01:02.280 --> 01:04.726
of genetic identicals we're monitoring,

01:04.840 --> 01:08.162
I can introduce you
to our most curated subject.

01:08.280 --> 01:10.442
Ladies and gentleman, meet

01:10.880 --> 01:12.166
Rachel Duncan.

01:14.040 --> 01:15.280
When I was six years old,

01:15.520 --> 01:18.205
I became the only LEDA aware
of the other clones.

01:18.640 --> 01:20.130
Dr Leekie shows me their files,

01:20.200 --> 01:23.124
so I can understand
how experiences determine traits.

01:23.760 --> 01:25.524
Do you see your own file too?

01:27.160 --> 01:28.571
Do you know your ID tag number?

01:33.360 --> 01:34.361
Rachel.

01:35.040 --> 01:36.530
779H41.

01:37.880 --> 01:41.009
The encrypted ID tags
are synthetic DNA sequences

01:41.080 --> 01:44.448
composed of four nucleotides,
which patent the clones.

01:45.040 --> 01:47.202
That's how you can tell
that I'm Rachel Duncan

01:47.280 --> 01:50.045
and not Lisa Glynn, 415K98,

01:50.720 --> 01:53.405
or Cosima Niehaus, 324521.

01:53.800 --> 01:55.006
(CHUCKLES)

01:59.160 --> 02:00.764
<i>WEST MORLAND: (ON VXDEO CALL)
Mitochondrial DNA</i>

02:01.520 --> 02:04.490
<i>is fundamental to the healing process,</i>

02:05.040 --> 02:07.884
<i>but it's only passed down by the mother.</i>

02:08.160 --> 02:11.209
<i>Our research into my anomalous longevity</i>

02:11.280 --> 02:12.964
<i>has only taken us so far.</i>

02:13.880 --> 02:15.325
<i>But now,</i>

02:15.480 --> 02:18.802
<i>thanks in large part to Rachel Duncan,</i>

02:18.920 --> 02:21.207
<i>we have found our Eve.</i>

02:21.840 --> 02:24.605
<i>Rachel, I'll let you take it from here.</i>

02:25.120 --> 02:26.246
(SCREEN BEEPS)

02:29.240 --> 02:32.005
You've all benefited from your seats
at this table.

02:32.680 --> 02:35.570
We owe a great debt to Mr Westmorland.

02:36.640 --> 02:38.961
I don't carry debts, Ms Duncan.

02:39.040 --> 02:40.201
RACHEL: Mr Al-Khatib,

02:40.720 --> 02:43.200
we freed your daughter
from a genetic heart defect.

02:44.000 --> 02:45.729
What is that worth to you?

02:47.280 --> 02:48.327
My mistake.

02:48.680 --> 02:49.841
I misspoke.

02:51.160 --> 02:53.527
Then, as you know, Dr Virginia Coady

02:53.600 --> 02:56.922
has taken over as head scientist
from my late mother.

02:57.320 --> 02:59.607
Our next phase with a LYN-28A subject

02:59.680 --> 03:02.843
is biopsies of her liver, lungs,
and stomach.

03:03.600 --> 03:04.647
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

03:05.720 --> 03:08.564
You heard P.T.
mention our modern-day Eve.

03:08.680 --> 03:09.681
Here she is.

03:19.360 --> 03:21.522
(TH EME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:55.600 --> 03:57.443
Why do I have to stay here
another night?

03:57.800 --> 03:59.006
To monitor your sleep.

03:59.320 --> 04:01.687
(SIGHS) The needles hurt
too much to sleep.

04:04.240 --> 04:05.321
We're nearly done with that.

04:05.800 --> 04:07.484
KIRA: And then I can go home?

04:07.920 --> 04:09.331
Yes, of course, you can.

04:09.400 --> 04:10.481
(DOOR BEEPS)

04:11.920 --> 04:12.921
Come along.

04:13.440 --> 04:15.488
Um, I have a present for you.

04:17.120 --> 04:18.724
It's a friendship bracelet.

04:20.839 --> 04:21.921
That's very sweet.

04:24.600 --> 04:26.489
I made one of these when I was your age

04:26.560 --> 04:28.164
for a friend at summer camp.

04:28.640 --> 04:29.846
Are you guys still friends?

04:30.400 --> 04:31.526
No.

04:33.440 --> 04:36.489
My mom moved me around too much
to keep friends, too.

04:43.160 --> 04:44.844
Can I call my mom to say good night?

04:45.360 --> 04:47.806
It's bedtime.
You can talk to her tomorrow.

04:48.840 --> 04:49.841
<i>Okay-</i>

04:52.400 --> 04:55.370
The Coast Guard found Cosima's boat
drifting offshore.

04:55.440 --> 04:56.441
Well...

04:57.160 --> 04:59.606
Till you find them,
don't assume they've drowned.

05:00.280 --> 05:02.931
Cosima's taken a large portion
of her cure.

05:03.480 --> 05:05.244
Air transport is ready
to take you to the island.

05:05.320 --> 05:06.924
Keep me updated on Kira.

05:07.320 --> 05:09.448
We've only just begun to collect
her and her eggs.

05:10.280 --> 05:12.203
SIMON: Her mother
keeps calling to talk to her.

05:12.880 --> 05:15.326
Tell Sarah tomorrow as well.

05:20.040 --> 05:21.087
Tomorrow?

05:21.560 --> 05:23.483
They took her away at bloody gunpoint.

05:23.560 --> 05:24.721
What are they doing to her?

05:25.520 --> 05:27.090
MRS S: It's my fault.
I should've stopped them.

05:27.480 --> 05:28.481
We're getting her back.

05:29.080 --> 05:30.445
S, we're not storming the gates.

05:30.520 --> 05:32.045
We need another way... Hey!

05:32.400 --> 05:34.004
Look, you were the one who taught me

05:34.080 --> 05:35.809
not to lose my head
when things get tough.

05:37.560 --> 05:38.686
We can do this.

05:39.240 --> 05:40.480
We just need to think.

05:43.200 --> 05:44.850
Just so you know,
I'm really not in the mood

05:44.920 --> 05:46.604
for any surprise late-night D&D.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.364
Dude, it's D&D in real life.

05:49.320 --> 05:51.607
- Hi.
-Oh, my God. Cosima.

05:52.600 --> 05:53.726
When did you...

05:53.880 --> 05:55.370
- Finally...
-COSMIA: Yeah.

05:56.480 --> 05:57.925
I'm so glad you're okay.

05:58.040 --> 06:00.486
We escaped in a boat
with only a map and compass.

06:00.720 --> 06:02.529
She was an amazing navigator.

06:02.760 --> 06:05.127
And then they put the boat in gear,
sent it off unmanned.

06:05.200 --> 06:06.770
- Totaljason Bourne.
-Yeah.

06:07.240 --> 06:08.241
I'm West Coast.

06:09.320 --> 06:12.005
- Cosima, you're home.
-Yeah.

06:12.440 --> 06:13.646
So is our cure.

06:14.400 --> 06:15.606
-(INHALES)
-(PHONE BEEPING)

06:15.760 --> 06:18.411
That's Sarah. I... I have brittle news.

06:19.520 --> 06:21.409
They're taking Kira's eggs?

06:21.640 --> 06:22.766
That's what they're doing?

06:22.840 --> 06:24.649
- COSIMA: (ON VIDEO CALL) I'm so sorry.
-When?

06:25.000 --> 06:26.126
How long do we have?

06:26.560 --> 06:28.483
<i>Well, you said that
they took her last night?</i>

06:28.760 --> 06:31.650
They'll need to give her hormone
injections before they can harvest.

06:31.720 --> 06:34.769
- I... It'll be at least another day.
-SARAH: Jesus.

06:34.920 --> 06:36.888
<i>She hasn't even had a period yet.</i>

06:37.080 --> 06:39.287
Yeah, well, we're born with all the eggs
we'll ever have.

06:39.360 --> 06:42.648
And technically,
they could extract them from infants.

06:42.720 --> 06:45.121
They're doing it again
to another generation of women.

06:45.200 --> 06:46.850
No, no, they're not.

06:46.960 --> 06:48.041
This is our window.

06:48.200 --> 06:51.329
Okay? Cosima, we need leverage
to get Kira back.

06:51.400 --> 06:53.562
<i>Yeah, um, okay. How about...</i>

06:53.960 --> 06:55.849
<i>Westmorland is a total fraud.</i>

06:56.080 --> 06:59.562
<i>I saw a picture of him
and Susan Duncan in 1967.</i>

06:59.640 --> 07:03.122
<i>He's just assumed this identity
to sell his story.</i>

07:03.280 --> 07:04.611
MRS S: I bloody knew it.

07:05.440 --> 07:08.728
Okay, well, Felix and Adele will send us
all this information

07:08.800 --> 07:10.086
on the Neo money trail.

07:10.160 --> 07:11.207
<i>We'll keep on that</i>

07:11.280 --> 07:13.806
<i>if you just go over everything
that I collected with the boys there.</i>

07:14.080 --> 07:15.605
Yes, good, done.

07:16.040 --> 07:18.122
We'll find out
who this bastard really is.

07:18.680 --> 07:20.330
<i>MASON". Oh, goodness.</i>

07:20.400 --> 07:21.686
<i>Cosima, I just got your message.</i>

07:21.760 --> 07:23.205
<i>I'm so happy you're back.</i>

07:23.360 --> 07:24.600
Hey, Alison.

07:25.200 --> 07:26.326
Where are you?

07:26.400 --> 07:28.243
<i>ALISON: California. I'm back tomorrow.</i>

07:28.400 --> 07:30.129
<i>But this is not about me.</i>

07:30.600 --> 07:32.045
<i>What is going on with Kira?</i>

07:34.160 --> 07:35.889
I'll fill you in, love,

07:35.960 --> 07:37.644
but leave the children with your mum.

07:39.200 --> 07:40.884
<i>Uh, one more thing.</i>

07:41.800 --> 07:43.882
<i>Virginia Coady is on the island.</i>

07:44.640 --> 07:47.484
<i>And I've got a feeling
that didn't end well for Susan.</i>

07:59.320 --> 08:00.321
Where is she?

08:00.520 --> 08:01.521
Beyond the arbour.

08:01.760 --> 08:03.330
(HELICOPTER FLYING OVERHEAD)

08:15.280 --> 08:18.329
<i>WESTMORLAND: Susan has shown me
she doesn't have the backbone,</i>

08:18.400 --> 08:21.165
<i>but you... You have proven yourself.</i>

08:21.880 --> 08:27.444
Will you join me at my side
to lead Neolution forward?

08:30.520 --> 08:31.567
Yes.

08:31.880 --> 08:32.961
Yes.

08:33.520 --> 08:36.808
I consider you my daughter.

08:50.920 --> 08:52.081
Hello, Rachel.

08:55.800 --> 08:57.290
Now, how are you holding up?

08:59.720 --> 09:01.404
She never believed in me.

09:01.800 --> 09:02.847
I know.

09:03.800 --> 09:05.086
I'm so sorry.

09:06.440 --> 09:07.521
Well...

09:08.240 --> 09:11.084
Virginia has been waiting to meet you.

09:14.120 --> 09:16.726
I offered her Susan's old lab,

09:16.800 --> 09:18.723
but she's nostalgic.

09:20.160 --> 09:22.970
Virginia Coady, meet Rachel Duncan.

09:25.120 --> 09:26.246
It's an honour.

09:27.880 --> 09:29.166
The sentiment is mutual.

09:29.760 --> 09:31.285
I've reviewed your work as a geneticist.

09:31.360 --> 09:32.600
It's impressive.

09:33.600 --> 09:35.364
Glad to be back from the abyss.

09:35.840 --> 09:37.842
I'm looking forward to working
with you and Kira.

09:37.960 --> 09:39.450
Helena too, soon.

09:39.960 --> 09:42.201
So, should we get to it then?

09:42.320 --> 09:46.291
Yes. Rachel, meet me in my office
after your examination.

09:47.160 --> 09:48.685
My examination?

09:49.160 --> 09:50.685
An endometrial biopsy

09:50.920 --> 09:52.922
to test the efficacy of the inoculation.

09:53.000 --> 09:54.968
We'll have the results tomorrow.

09:55.040 --> 09:58.487
Virginia wants to cure
the remaining LEDAs

09:58.600 --> 09:59.601
as much as you do.

10:02.280 --> 10:03.691
I'll give you a moment to change.

10:07.200 --> 10:11.603
<i>WESTMORLAND". You are no longer 779H41</i>

10:11.680 --> 10:13.603
or Neolution property.

10:14.160 --> 10:17.960
This document legally emancipates you.

10:19.720 --> 10:20.926
No more monitors.

10:22.800 --> 10:23.881
You're free.

10:24.480 --> 10:25.561
Go home.

10:30.040 --> 10:31.166
(SIGHS)

11:02.120 --> 11:04.521
Any cramps since your inoculation?

11:05.160 --> 11:06.446
RACHEL: No.

11:06.520 --> 11:08.329
A hopeful sign that it worked?

11:13.320 --> 11:14.924
Stabilise the LEDA subjects,

11:15.000 --> 11:17.606
so we can finally
use them as a baseline.

11:18.040 --> 11:21.203
Your priorities are refreshing
after Susan's.

11:21.280 --> 11:23.089
Oh, she was always preaching.

11:24.120 --> 11:26.248
You can thank me
for putting an end to that.

11:28.160 --> 11:29.207
Scooch forward.

11:31.280 --> 11:33.442
You can expect
a few uncomfortable pinches.

11:34.640 --> 11:36.404
Just lay back.

11:43.160 --> 11:44.207
DR ALDOUS: Hmm.

11:45.000 --> 11:46.525
No obvious irregularities.

11:47.080 --> 11:48.969
- Should I still biopsy?
-Yes.

11:50.120 --> 11:51.326
Is that necessary?

11:57.120 --> 12:01.011
Does this have something to do
with 528M32's latest results?

12:03.200 --> 12:05.362
I'm closely monitoring her disease.

12:06.560 --> 12:08.324
You never called it that before.

12:11.120 --> 12:13.851
Has another clone developed
her same uterine growths?

12:17.520 --> 12:19.522
Symptoms appeared in two other LEDAs.

12:22.880 --> 12:24.211
This will pinch.

12:25.640 --> 12:26.766
(GROAN5)

12:28.840 --> 12:31.081
Your treatments on her
have been useless.

12:31.920 --> 12:33.046
She coughed up blood.

12:33.520 --> 12:36.524
There's no manual for
treating disease in synthetic DNA.

12:38.560 --> 12:40.210
We'll know more
when we have further data.

12:41.560 --> 12:43.164
Meaning when another falls ill?

12:45.120 --> 12:46.565
When will we have my results?

12:47.240 --> 12:48.730
I'm not permitted to share them.

12:49.800 --> 12:51.131
Don't patronise me.

12:51.760 --> 12:53.091
I have a right to know.

12:53.680 --> 12:54.681
(scoffs)

12:55.280 --> 12:56.884
You're not exempt
from the experiment, Rachel.

13:07.000 --> 13:08.490
All done.

13:08.560 --> 13:10.210
And I didn't see any irregularities.

13:10.920 --> 13:11.967
So that's good.

13:13.520 --> 13:15.648
May I have some privacy, please.

13:16.880 --> 13:17.961
Of course.

13:44.000 --> 13:45.286
Hey, do you remember this guy?

13:46.680 --> 13:47.761
Ian Van Lier?

13:47.840 --> 13:49.046
Yeah, at Brightborn.

13:49.120 --> 13:51.566
He's the one who sent Delphine
to the island after she was shot.

13:51.640 --> 13:54.246
Remember he talked about a board,
a kind of corporate cabal,

13:54.320 --> 13:56.448
-who meet to push the Neo agenda.
-Yeah.

13:56.520 --> 13:58.807
Well, if everyone on the island
were into P.T.'s myth,

13:59.240 --> 14:01.368
do you think
the Neolution board did too?

14:01.680 --> 14:05.890
Okay, so whoever he was had to disappear
for him to become P.T.

14:06.040 --> 14:09.442
Yeah, he and Susan recruited Coady
at Cambridge in the '70s.

14:10.080 --> 14:12.162
Student registration from Susan's
time there is a mountain.

14:12.240 --> 14:15.403
Susan and P.T. started resurrecting
Neolution before 1967.

14:15.480 --> 14:18.962
So, start looking for history majors
and then science and philosophy.

14:19.040 --> 14:22.010
That's how he spun his persona.

14:22.080 --> 14:23.127
All right.

14:23.280 --> 14:26.011
White Cambridge nerds who died
in the 1960s

14:26.400 --> 14:27.765
present yourselves.

14:29.280 --> 14:31.328
Van Lier is director at Dyad,

14:31.400 --> 14:35.007
Blue Zone Cosmetics,
and 11 biotech companies.

14:35.080 --> 14:37.686
According to Adele, they're all
funnelling funds into a Dyad shell,

14:37.760 --> 14:40.604
which has made payments
of hundreds of millions of dollars

14:40.680 --> 14:43.286
to a Kuwaiti consulting firm.

14:43.520 --> 14:44.681
"Consulting."

14:44.760 --> 14:46.649
What are they using that for, bribes?

14:46.720 --> 14:48.609
Well, I don't know,
but if it's a slush fund,

14:48.680 --> 14:51.126
according to Adele,
it's controlled by this man here.

14:53.160 --> 14:54.446
Hashem Al-Khatib.

14:54.520 --> 14:56.010
Mmm-hmm. Follow him.

14:57.320 --> 14:58.321
(EXHALES)

14:58.960 --> 14:59.961
(SIGHS)

15:01.680 --> 15:03.682
Kira will find a way to call, love.

15:04.160 --> 15:05.241
We still have time.

15:05.600 --> 15:07.204
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

15:07.480 --> 15:08.481
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

15:19.760 --> 15:20.807
(DOOR OPENS)

15:21.240 --> 15:23.083
Welcome home...

15:24.440 --> 15:25.851
Oh, wow, Alison.

15:25.920 --> 15:27.081
Oh, God, Kira.

15:27.560 --> 15:29.244
I can't imagine
what Sarah's going through.

15:31.040 --> 15:34.283
Yeah, well, we'll support them
in every way we can.

15:34.360 --> 15:35.407
Yes, oh, yes.

15:35.480 --> 15:38.245
God, I feel so guilty.
Our kids are so safe

15:38.320 --> 15:42.166
and Sarah is always at risk
because of this fluke of nature.

15:42.240 --> 15:43.241
Yeah, I...

15:44.280 --> 15:45.281
Ali...

15:46.280 --> 15:47.281
What?

15:47.560 --> 15:48.721
I'm sorry, your hair.

15:49.240 --> 15:50.241
Do you like it?

15:50.760 --> 15:52.762
It's artsy.

15:52.840 --> 15:53.841
Yes.

15:53.920 --> 15:55.251
- And purple.
-Yes.

15:55.320 --> 15:57.891
I wanted something creative and free,
you know.

15:57.960 --> 16:00.725
I... I met this Jungian whojust...

16:01.880 --> 16:04.201
- Lives in that place.
-A who?

16:04.280 --> 16:05.281
AJUflgian.

16:05.360 --> 16:06.407
U/Ajungianlu?

16:06.480 --> 16:08.562
A practiser of Carljung.

16:08.960 --> 16:10.121
- Yeah, yeah.
-Hmm.

16:10.200 --> 16:12.521
And I just am so much better
at being present now.

16:13.480 --> 16:15.403
(STUTTERING)

16:15.960 --> 16:17.007
Honey!

16:24.880 --> 16:26.245
I missed you so much, Alison.

16:26.320 --> 16:27.321
(CHUCKLES)

16:28.440 --> 16:29.930
- And I missed this.
-(CHUCKLES)

16:30.000 --> 16:31.001
Oh, ouch!

16:31.080 --> 16:32.161
What did I do?

16:32.640 --> 16:34.005
Nothing. I just, um...

16:34.080 --> 16:37.323
I did a little something to commemorate

16:38.200 --> 16:39.770
the transformation.

16:39.840 --> 16:40.921
Whoa!

16:41.960 --> 16:43.121
"Liver deep."

16:43.360 --> 16:45.124
-"Live deep."
-Live... Live deep.

16:45.200 --> 16:46.361
- Yeah, there it is.
-Yeah.

16:46.440 --> 16:47.965
- It's a Thoreau quote.
-Uh-huh.

16:48.040 --> 16:50.520
It means live deep
and suck the marrow out of life.

16:51.120 --> 16:53.327
(ALISON CHUCKLES AND SQUEALS)

16:53.400 --> 16:54.731
MA N : <i>(O</i> N P H O N <i>E) We 'll make preparations.</i>

16:54.800 --> 16:58.247
<i>Kira's hormone stimulation is on track
and we will be ready tomorrow.</i>

16:58.320 --> 17:00.687
WESTMORLAND: It's not going to be
an issue, is it?

17:00.760 --> 17:02.046
The way they've bonded.

17:02.120 --> 17:03.690
<i>There is an attachment, to be sure.</i>

17:03.760 --> 17:05.728
<i>But I don't foresee it clouding
her judgment.</i>

17:05.800 --> 17:07.723
Yes, well, keep me updated.

17:07.800 --> 17:08.847
(PHONE BEEPS)

17:11.440 --> 17:12.601
Was that Simon?

17:12.680 --> 17:15.080
I have many people who report to me.

17:16.040 --> 17:17.326
Please sit.

17:18.000 --> 17:20.367
How was your examination?

17:21.240 --> 17:24.847
In the future, I prefer to choose
my own physician.

17:25.480 --> 17:28.006
And I expect advance notice.

17:28.079 --> 17:29.491
As you wish.

17:30.960 --> 17:33.361
Could you give me an update on Kira?

17:34.640 --> 17:39.487
I estimate that we can harvest her eggs
within 24 hours.

17:40.440 --> 17:41.601
And after she has recovered,

17:41.680 --> 17:45.241
we can begin studying
her healing at deeper tissues.

17:47.280 --> 17:50.170
You've grown quite fond of Kira,
haven't you?

17:52.000 --> 17:54.924
She's a special child,
but I assure you I am unwavering.

17:55.920 --> 17:57.001
Good.

17:57.080 --> 18:00.084
After the surgery,
I want you to bring her to the island.

18:01.440 --> 18:06.162
But we have the resources at Dyad
to move on to the next steps.

18:07.160 --> 18:09.128
I'd prefer to have her here.

18:09.200 --> 18:11.646
It is our change of tactic with Sarah,
which has brought her in.

18:11.720 --> 18:14.803
On whose behalf are you arguing now?

18:17.240 --> 18:19.447
Your transport has been arranged.

18:21.560 --> 18:22.686
You know best.

18:26.280 --> 18:27.645
Who is that?

18:27.720 --> 18:29.484
Virginia's guest.

18:37.760 --> 18:39.649
Unlock his cuffs and leave us.

18:46.720 --> 18:48.131
Is all this really necessary?

18:48.880 --> 18:50.291
I thought we had an agreement.

18:50.840 --> 18:51.921
You're a traitor, Mark.

18:52.440 --> 18:53.566
You're lucky we need you.

18:55.160 --> 18:56.685
You said you'd cure me,

18:57.520 --> 18:58.851
if I helped you.

19:04.120 --> 19:06.122
Love makes you want to live, doesn't it?

19:07.320 --> 19:10.210
Gracie can't look at me
without searching for symptoms.

19:11.240 --> 19:12.969
I can't imagine her all alone.

19:13.720 --> 19:15.404
Well, I'm sorry, she's not here to help.

19:17.440 --> 19:20.683
But I need you to give me
an ejaculate sample.

19:26.280 --> 19:28.044
That wasn't part of our deal.

19:28.560 --> 19:29.971
You've got plenty to spare.

19:32.280 --> 19:35.045
Now, you said you had information.

19:37.680 --> 19:40.001
I think I can help you find Helena.

20:03.080 --> 20:04.366
What are you doing here?

20:45.600 --> 20:46.761
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

20:51.240 --> 20:52.321
(DOOR OPENS)

20:53.680 --> 20:54.681
(GASPING)

21:01.000 --> 21:02.809
I was looking for you to say goodbye.

21:03.800 --> 21:04.881
Goodbye.

21:29.720 --> 21:30.881
(MOBILE RINGING)

21:34.400 --> 21:36.084
Rachel, you're still here.

21:37.360 --> 21:38.885
I thought you might like to read this.

21:41.000 --> 21:42.968
An autopsy report. (CHUCKLES)

21:43.680 --> 21:44.841
I took initiative.

21:50.120 --> 21:53.681
The microscopic examination revealed
the growths have spread

21:53.760 --> 21:57.321
to her thoracic cavity,
even her kidneys.

22:04.800 --> 22:06.325
RACHEL: 528M32.

22:06.880 --> 22:08.120
DR ALDOUS: Oh, my God, Rachel.

22:09.120 --> 22:10.451
- You killed her.
-(CLICKS TONGUE)

22:11.000 --> 22:14.482
While you were sitting on your hands
waiting for her to die naturally,

22:14.560 --> 22:15.686
when we need a cure.

22:17.280 --> 22:19.328
I won't be shut out of my medical file.

22:19.920 --> 22:21.001
It's my body.

22:21.080 --> 22:23.367
DR ALDOUS: Her name is Miriam Johnson.

22:23.440 --> 22:25.124
She was creative, a musician.

22:25.200 --> 22:26.281
RACHEL: She was homeless.

22:26.360 --> 22:28.727
And the mother you put her with
was a drunk!

22:30.200 --> 22:31.531
You raised me to be objective.

22:31.880 --> 22:33.291
Neolution raised you.

22:34.440 --> 22:35.441
Here...

22:36.200 --> 22:37.611
In a corporation.

22:40.120 --> 22:41.281
What are you?

22:47.400 --> 22:48.561
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

22:55.320 --> 22:57.288
Rachel, how was your trip?

22:58.920 --> 23:00.843
Take her to her room. I have work to do.

23:00.920 --> 23:02.604
You said I could call my mom.

23:09.080 --> 23:10.684
Her follicles have swollen.

23:10.760 --> 23:12.000
SIMON: Right on target.

23:12.080 --> 23:13.889
Yes, good.

23:15.040 --> 23:16.724
Let her talk to her mother.

23:16.800 --> 23:18.370
Set up a video call.

23:19.720 --> 23:21.085
Keep a close eye on them.

23:33.400 --> 23:36.210
MARK: Ira must've been raised
much differently than the rest of us.

23:38.520 --> 23:40.761
How did you choose which one of us
would go?

23:42.360 --> 23:43.361
The truth?

23:44.720 --> 23:45.721
I drew straws.

23:48.240 --> 23:49.605
Am I the only one left?

23:53.000 --> 23:54.161
Your brothers, they...

23:55.880 --> 23:57.006
They all...

23:58.440 --> 23:59.441
(SIGHS)

24:00.720 --> 24:02.404
(SNIFFLES AND SIGHS)

24:06.320 --> 24:07.924
(SNIFFLING)

24:14.080 --> 24:15.411
Thank you for trusting me.

24:16.200 --> 24:17.406
You're doing the right thing, Mark.

24:25.200 --> 24:28.443
Honey, are you sure you don't want
to just store your craft supplies,

24:28.520 --> 24:29.521
instead of donating them?

24:29.600 --> 24:31.125
No, I'm done with crafts.

24:31.200 --> 24:33.089
- Really?
-Yes.

24:33.160 --> 24:35.367
- All of your scissors?
-Mmm-hmm.

24:35.440 --> 24:37.920
The point of art is
to lose control, Donnie.

24:38.000 --> 24:39.411
To reveal your inner chaos.

24:39.480 --> 24:41.767
I'm uncovering my shadow self.

24:42.680 --> 24:45.081
And is that your inner artist
or something?

24:45.560 --> 24:48.131
Could be an artist, could just be
the dark parts of yourself.

24:48.360 --> 24:49.930
The things...

24:50.000 --> 24:52.685
Subconscious desires
that aren't necessarily good.

24:52.760 --> 24:56.765
Well, if they're bad,
don't we want to keep them in the dark?

24:57.720 --> 25:00.769
No, because then they manifest
in behaviour.

25:00.840 --> 25:04.322
In my drinking,
in my need to control everything.

25:04.400 --> 25:05.925
So, this is about your drinking?

25:06.000 --> 25:10.369
Drinking is the effect
of the unexplored shadow self.

25:10.440 --> 25:12.488
And that's a Korg.

25:12.560 --> 25:13.721
Yes.

25:13.800 --> 25:17.122
So, wait, the craft room
is becoming the music room?

25:18.240 --> 25:20.049
That sounds pretty cool.
I could get down with that.

25:20.120 --> 25:22.407
- We could lay down some tasty tracks.
-Mmm-hmm.

25:22.480 --> 25:23.925
Should I get a bass?

25:24.000 --> 25:25.161
I don't know.

25:25.760 --> 25:26.841
Do you want a bass?

25:27.520 --> 25:29.090
Okay, no bass. Drums?

25:29.640 --> 25:31.404
Donnie, this is exactly
what I'm talking about.

25:32.720 --> 25:35.405
Bass, drums, I'm not going to tell you
what to do any more.

25:35.840 --> 25:36.921
I don't need to.

25:38.720 --> 25:39.881
<i>Ream]?</i>

25:39.960 --> 25:41.724
(TUNE PLAYING ON KEYBOARD)

25:48.160 --> 25:50.447
They gave me lots of time
to write my story.

25:50.520 --> 25:51.931
SARAH: (ON VIDEO CALL) Good <i>good.</i>

25:52.440 --> 25:54.966
The last page I saw, mouse...
(CLICKS TONGUE)

25:56.080 --> 25:57.889
No, elephant went smoosh

25:57.960 --> 26:00.645
-and mouse went whoosh. Is that right?
-Mmm-hmm.

26:01.200 --> 26:02.770
<i>Then, mouse got lost</i>

26:03.400 --> 26:04.731
<i>and the sun went away.</i>

26:04.800 --> 26:08.361
And elephant was the only one
left to play.

26:09.960 --> 26:11.689
And this is the last page.

26:14.400 --> 26:17.722
<i>Mouse cried and asked to return
to the sand.</i>

26:17.800 --> 26:21.168
<i>But elephant said she belonged
in Wonderland.</i>

26:25.920 --> 26:26.921
Is that the end?

26:27.480 --> 26:28.481
<i>I don't know.</i>

26:28.560 --> 26:30.164
I don't think that's the end.

26:30.240 --> 26:34.529
I think when you get here we'll...
We'll write the end of that, yeah?

26:34.600 --> 26:35.806
<i>We'll work on it together.</i>

26:37.080 --> 26:38.127
<i>okay-</i>

26:38.200 --> 26:39.201
Say goodbye now, Kira.

26:41.200 --> 26:42.929
I miss you so much.

26:47.760 --> 26:50.206
I love you, more than anything.

26:50.280 --> 26:51.964
I've never been so proud of you.

26:52.400 --> 26:53.845
(sesame)

26:56.880 --> 26:58.211
(SIGHS)

27:02.160 --> 27:05.004
Rachel's the elephant,
and Wonderland is the island.

27:08.160 --> 27:10.003
They're taking Kira to the island?

27:10.640 --> 27:11.846
<i>Coach's there.</i>

27:13.320 --> 27:14.845
(GLASS CLINKING)

27:25.240 --> 27:26.321
(BEEPS)

27:33.480 --> 27:34.561
(REMOTE BEEPS)

27:36.480 --> 27:37.481
(REMOTE BEEPS)

27:40.240 --> 27:41.287
(REMOTE BEEPS)

28:01.760 --> 28:03.171
(MOBILE RINGING)

28:10.520 --> 28:11.885
Mr Westmorland.

28:12.600 --> 28:13.647
<i>How can I help you?</i>

28:13.720 --> 28:18.681
Rachel, I'm just checking in
to make sure that you're all right.

28:20.000 --> 28:21.365
Why wouldn't I be?

28:21.440 --> 28:24.967
Well, I have asked you to do something
that you don't want to do.

28:26.320 --> 28:28.288
I would do anything for you.

28:29.720 --> 28:31.449
<i>When I was a child at Dyad,</i>

28:31.880 --> 28:33.370
I was so naive,

28:33.840 --> 28:36.241
I asked Leekie
if I could call him "Dad".

28:38.880 --> 28:40.166
Isn't that funny?

28:40.280 --> 28:42.931
<i>WESTMORLAND". Well, you've transcended
that too, daughter.</i>

28:43.000 --> 28:46.163
Which is why I've shared
all my secrets with you.

28:50.600 --> 28:52.011
Thank you for calling.

28:53.360 --> 28:56.125
<i>You don't have to worry.
We're about to proceed.</i>

29:10.760 --> 29:11.761
(DOOR BEEPS)

29:21.680 --> 29:22.806
Are you okay?

29:24.000 --> 29:25.081
(RACHEL SNIFFLES)

29:27.720 --> 29:29.051
Who hurt you?

29:35.440 --> 29:36.601
All of them.

29:39.520 --> 29:40.806
SIMON: The doctors are ready.

29:42.880 --> 29:44.211
It's what P.T. wants.

29:44.560 --> 29:45.891
I will give her the sedative.

29:47.640 --> 29:50.041
I was the one who brought Kira to Dyad.

29:52.480 --> 29:54.687
I will be the last face she sees here.

29:56.640 --> 29:57.926
<i>WESTMORLAND". Hello, Kira.</i>

29:58.000 --> 29:59.764
<i>I'm Mr Westmorland.</i>

30:01.040 --> 30:06.171
<i>Do you have any idea
how important you are?</i>

30:07.080 --> 30:09.367
I just want to go home to my mom.

30:09.440 --> 30:14.685
<i>And I'm counting down the minutes,
until we meet in person.</i>

30:21.120 --> 30:23.009
All right, we've got nine obituaries

30:23.080 --> 30:25.481
for male students who died
during Susan's time there.

30:25.560 --> 30:27.210
These are the faces we have so far.

30:27.280 --> 30:29.886
Timothy Midwell, died 1969.

30:29.960 --> 30:31.007
Alcohol poisoning.

30:31.080 --> 30:32.161
No.

30:32.640 --> 30:35.769
Henry Ganard, died '68.
He fell from a punt and drowned.

30:35.840 --> 30:37.729
Probably also alcohol poisoning. No.

30:38.440 --> 30:42.570
Winston Tralley, died '65,
rugby accident.

30:42.640 --> 30:43.641
No!

30:43.720 --> 30:44.801
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

30:46.760 --> 30:47.921
Holy shit.

30:48.880 --> 30:50.120
(MOBILE BEEPING)

30:52.560 --> 30:55.131
Cosima, please tell me
you have something.

30:55.680 --> 30:56.920
We got him, Sarah.

31:38.320 --> 31:39.731
(MOBILE RINGING)

31:41.400 --> 31:42.765
john Patrick Mathieson.

31:42.840 --> 31:44.524
<i>He's not 170.</i>

31:44.600 --> 31:48.366
<i>He was born in Texas in 1939
to an oil tycoon.</i>

31:48.440 --> 31:50.363
<i>Silver spoon so far up his arse,</i>

31:50.440 --> 31:53.046
he could afford the ego it took
to do that shit.

31:54.640 --> 31:56.563
I never knew his real name.

31:56.640 --> 31:58.529
But you knew he was a fraud.

31:59.880 --> 32:02.804
Fraud? We're all frauds.

32:04.280 --> 32:05.645
Get on to the board.

32:06.760 --> 32:09.047
Rachel, you knew his secret.
What about your board?

32:09.120 --> 32:10.565
<i>How are they going to react to this?</i>

32:11.320 --> 32:13.448
Do you think they would listen to you,

32:15.160 --> 32:16.764
a nuisance clone?

32:18.000 --> 32:21.163
Rachel, I know
what you're planning to do to Kira.

32:22.120 --> 32:25.124
What you're planning to do with her eggs
and taking her away.

32:25.200 --> 32:26.565
She needs her family.

32:27.080 --> 32:28.241
You needed...

32:28.320 --> 32:29.526
You needed your family.

32:29.600 --> 32:32.604
<i>And he took them away from you
as an experiment.</i>

32:32.680 --> 32:34.330
<i>Don't let that happen to Kira.</i>

32:34.400 --> 32:35.765
Let her come home.

32:44.720 --> 32:46.768
It's out of my hands, Sarah.

32:47.480 --> 32:50.086
- Please, no, Rachel!
-(LINE DISCONNECTS)

33:19.520 --> 33:20.567
(DOOR BEEPS)

33:26.640 --> 33:27.641
Drink.

33:30.560 --> 33:32.881
Did you hate being studied
when you were my age?

33:35.280 --> 33:36.520
I don't remember.

33:39.000 --> 33:40.240
Did you get used to it?

33:41.160 --> 33:42.161
Yes.

33:52.360 --> 33:53.646
Why don't you run?

33:55.240 --> 33:56.366
Where would I go?

34:06.600 --> 34:07.886
My mum used to do that.

34:14.120 --> 34:15.645
- Drink.
-(KIRA WHINES)

34:15.719 --> 34:17.927
Kira, be a good girl.

34:18.000 --> 34:19.047
Drink.

34:45.560 --> 34:48.005
Sarah is attempting to blackmail us,

34:48.760 --> 34:53.482
with fraudulent information
to invalidate Mr Westmorland's age.

34:54.600 --> 34:55.761
They faked this.

34:55.840 --> 34:58.207
She knows we're not returning Kira.

34:59.080 --> 35:00.525
I'll take care of them.

35:00.600 --> 35:02.921
Don't hesitate, Simon.

35:24.080 --> 35:26.924
-(KNOCKS AT DOOR)
-It's Art. Don't worry, I'm alone.

35:31.440 --> 35:32.646
What the hell are you doing here?

35:34.320 --> 35:35.446
You won't believe it.

36:05.320 --> 36:06.651
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

36:13.600 --> 36:14.726
(BEEPS)

36:47.720 --> 36:49.210
(MOBILE RINGING)

36:51.920 --> 36:52.921
<i>SIMON: They're not here.</i>

36:55.280 --> 36:56.964
<i>WESTMORLAND". You need to return at once.</i>

37:07.640 --> 37:08.641
(RAPID BEEPING)

37:16.200 --> 37:17.361
MRS S: Kira!

37:17.440 --> 37:18.566
What did you do to her?

37:18.640 --> 37:20.130
She's sedated. She's fine.

37:20.880 --> 37:21.881
Let's go, Siobhan.

37:24.480 --> 37:25.606
Thank you.

37:29.040 --> 37:30.610
(MOBILE RINGING)

37:38.960 --> 37:40.371
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

37:45.600 --> 37:46.647
(COMPUTER CHIMES)

38:07.800 --> 38:09.404
(MOBILE RINGING)

38:11.280 --> 38:12.281
(GROAN5)

38:15.560 --> 38:16.641
(MOBILE CONTINUES RINGING)

38:25.920 --> 38:27.046
(RINGING STOPS)

38:34.000 --> 38:35.081
(GLASS SHATTERING)

38:59.040 --> 39:00.041
(RACHEL GROANS)

39:02.080 --> 39:03.605
(GROANING)

39:05.320 --> 39:07.163
(GROANING IN PAIN)

39:22.880 --> 39:24.291
(GROANING CONTINUES)

39:34.440 --> 39:35.771
(GLASS CLIN KS)

39:38.080 --> 39:39.923
(GROANING)

39:42.160 --> 39:44.128
(PAIN ED GROANING CONTINUES)

39:50.160 --> 39:52.606
Ladies and gentleman, are you ready
to raise some hell with the Wizard?

39:52.680 --> 39:53.920
Let me hear you say yeah!

39:54.000 --> 39:55.411
(ALL CHEERING)

39:55.480 --> 39:57.005
<i># My love isn't tainted
It's just complicated</i>

39:57.080 --> 39:58.764
<i># We're saving the world
from down in the basement</i>

39:58.840 --> 40:00.729
<i># I saw the truth
I just couldn't face it</i>

40:00.800 --> 40:02.564
<i># All of these people,
They've been duplicated</i>

40:02.640 --> 40:04.369
<i># But they can't contain us
We're breaking the cages</i>

40:04.440 --> 40:06.204
<i># Lab rats got out of the mazes</i>

40:07.000 --> 40:08.411
<i># Tainted love</i>

40:08.480 --> 40:10.164
<i># Oh-oh-oh-ooh</i>

40:10.240 --> 40:13.369
<i># This tainted love you've given</i>

40:13.440 --> 40:16.444
<i># Take my tears and
that's not nearly all #</i>

40:16.520 --> 40:18.648
Hello, Siobhan. Welcome home.
